main event: A bluish white object resembling an electric fluorescent formation was observed near Santa Rosa Island, Florida, on January 16, 1961. The object descended, broke into many pieces, and then faded out.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be between 15 to 20 feet long., It was seen for about 5 minutes., The observation was classified as ground-visual., Several witnesses reported different sizes of the object., The conclusion suggested it was likely a meteor breaking up in the atmosphere.
sighted object: a bluish white object resembling an electric fluorescent formation
